Who: CYCLONUS, Hydras
Location: Black Fortress - Throne Room

> Hydras growled in pain and said "It seems that I need a cr... My Cr. I need
> to reach there... I need your help Cyclonus... What had happened with that
> treacherous rat and with our prisioners... what happened with the primes?"

Cyclonus stepped over to Hydras and carefully helped him to his feet.
"Tuscon has escaped, as well as the other Maximals." Cyclonus said
sorrowfully. "Rodimus . . . I am not sure."

Cyclonus paused as he looked over Hydras' injuries as best he could,
"As for Perceptor." Cyclonus paused again as he looked at Hydras, not
sure how exactly he felt about the Predacon scientist, "Perceptor
looked to be siding with Rodimus. When we found him he was in
conversation with him, as if planning something."

Cyclonus continued to help Hydras, "There was an explosion, it looked
like one of Perceptors'.  That was how the bots escaped. The explosion
blocked us from reaching Tuscon and the others. I absorbed what I
could of it, but I don't know." Cyclonus shrugged painfully, the
extent of his own injuries showing themselves.

"I didn't see any sign of Rodimus after that, although the explosion
opened up the tunnel that Scorponok had used to tunnel over here
several months ago from the Ark."
